IRS990.MissionDesc: To promote pro bono service and public interest law.
IRS990.Desc: During the year, the organization hosted programs and panels to promote pro bono and public-interest law, trainings for pro bono and public-interest lawyers, best practices in pro bono, public-interest law careers, fellowship opportunities, and mentoring.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Officer directors etc family relationship Part VI line 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Two members of the Board are married to each other.Given the nature of the Organizations work, Board members are often employed by the same organization and have a business relationship.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990 governing body review Part VI line 11
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The IRS Form 990 is prepared by an independent CPA and is reviewed with the staff prior to sharing with the full Board.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Conflict of interest policy compliance Part VI line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The conflict of interest policy requires that board members disclose any potential or actual direct or indirect financial interest in any decisions being taken by Washington Council of Lawyers. If a conflict of interest exists, the board member involved is prohibited from voting on the issue.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: CEO executive director top management comp Part VI line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: As part of the budgeting processes, a committee of the Board recomends a compensation amount that the full Board votes on.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Other officer or key employee compensation Part VI line 15b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: As part of the budgeting processes, a committee of the Board recomends a compensation amount that the full Board votes on.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Governing documents etc available to public Part VI line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: These documents are available upon request.

Primary Exempt Purpose: To promote pro-bono service and public interest law.Statement of Program Service Accomplishments: During the year, the Organization hosted programs and panels to promote pro-bono, public interest law programs focused on government lawyer pro-bono servives, best-practices in pro-bono, public interest law careers, fellowship opportunities and mentoring.The Organization also offerred litigation skills training to over 200 public interest minded lawyers.
